assetDescriptions.description:
It's Time to RUN The ATL!

YEAR 9 of Atlanta's favorite Road Race , The REI ATL Relay, 10K & 20K produced runningnerds Run Social Atlanta & benefitting Castleberry Hill Nieghborhood Association!  

Get your squad together and run in the 20K Relay (4 Runner/Walker team each completing a 5K Leg).

You can also participate in the road race as a 10K or 20K Individual Runner/Walker!

2020 Race Features:
--New DesignCustom Finishers Medals for Relay, 10K & 20K Participants!
--Awesome Run The ATL race shirt for each participant
--Post Race VIP Experience at iwi Fresh Garden Day Spa 

       --BIGGEST Medal & VIP Experience at iwi Fresh & Atlanta Hot Shave Included with 20K Registration!

--Certified AJC Peachtree Qualifier 10K Course
--Castleberry Hill Block Party and Run Social Atlanta sponsor give aways
--Top finisher awards for Relay Divisions, 10K, & 20K Age Groups
--Awards for Best Team Name & Best Dressed Teams
....and much much more TBA!

Relay Team Divisions:
Women & Men Open,
Women & Men Masters,
Mixed Open & Masters,
Youth (16 & Under Mixed)

Race Caps:

125 Relay Teams

200 10K

100 20K

Event details and schedule

Packet Pick-Up and On-Site Registration Events!

There will be no RACE DAY PACKET PICK UP OR RACE DAY REGISTRATION FOR THIS EVENT!

Tuesday, August 25th

The ATL CincoK Course Preview
Pratice Run & Packet Pick Up
6:30-8pm
No Mas Cantina
180 Walker Street SW

-join us for our 9th annual practice run event hosted by No Mas Cantina. Preview the route, get first hand race day info, enjoy some of the best Mexican food in ATL, AND...pick up your race day packet!!
-----
Wednesday, August 26th
Get Fresh for The ATL 
Packet Pick Up
4-7pm
iwi Fresh Garden Day Spa & Atlanta Hot Shave
341 Nelson Street SW, Atlanta, GA 30313

-Pick up your race packet and enjoy iwi Fresh & Atlanta Hot Shave specials and receive a special Get Fresh gift bag!!
-----
Thursday, August 27th
Gear up for The ATL 
Packet Pick Up
4-7pm
TBD

-Run Social give aways, discount on all your race day needs.
-----
Friday, August 28th
Last Minute Prep for The ATL
Packet Pick Up
12-7pmTBD

-Last Chance for Run Social give aways, discount on all your race day needs.

There will be NO RACE DAY PACKET PICK UP OR REGISTRATION. Yes, you can have a friend pick up for you. If a registered participant cannot attend of our the 4 packet pick up events or arrange for a friend to pick up for them, please contact runningnerds@gmail.com by Thursday, August 27th. Please make every effort to pick up your packet in advance. Thank you!!!

Let's go ATL!!!

 

 

Race Day Schedule:

Saturday, August 29th

GPS Location for Race Day Activities: 101 Centennial Olympic Park Dr. SW, Atlanta GA 30313

(101 Walker Street, Atlanta, GA 30313 also works -street changes names at our intersection)

6:15am Pre-Race Festivites Begin

7:00am Gun Start for Relay 1st Leg, 10K & 20K!

8-11am Post Race Brunch at No Mas & VIP Experience at iwi Fresh Garden Day Spa

Castleberry Hill - Atlanta, GA 30313

 

Parking Info:

Best: MARTA - CNN/Philips Arena is Best Exit

LYFT & UBER Services

 

Good: Neighborhood Parking in Castleberry Hill

No Mas Upper Lot

More details will be included in participant emails

X Challenge “Lion Templar Medal” Special Edition 13.1M/10k/5k/1k Remote-Run

Remote Race, Challenges & Extra Medals (Remote Race)

This means that site you can choose whatever you prefer. This can be at park, beach, stadium, GYM another race, favorite place, treadmill, near your town. Also free feel to share your experiences unload photos or images of your town. Also free feel to share your experiences unload photos or images of your run. You can run own distances Half Marathon/10k/5k1k any time, any state. Depend of your lifestyle. Is not a Live Event.

 

More info about remote races series: www.runners2life.com

All registered participants will receive a Medal

When: August 28th to August 31st

Who: All ages, all people, walkers are welcome.

Where: Any Place any city any town.

Shipping Delivery Date: Week of August 31st

 

Challenges: Options Multi-Medal Packs.

 

Double Down: Option A:

X Medal + Turkey Trot Medal = $39.99

Double Down: Option B:

Halloween Medal + “X” Medal = $39.99

Double Down: Option C

Freedom Medal + X medal = $39.99

Double Down: Option D

X Medal + Race of Dead Medal = $39.99

Trio: Four medals pack. $59.99

Halloween Medal + Pizza Medal + X medal + Extra medal = $59.99 (four medals total)

Only Medal INTERNATIONAL; Canada, South America, Europe, Asia, Australia:

Price $45

Challenge “The Lion Templar Medal 7” inches.

Complete the challenge of survivors and earn free the Lion Templar Medal:

In this pack you got nine medals one transaction. (Not t-shirts included)

Price: $99.99

Event details and schedule

Is a Remote race you can run anywhere any city, any town, park, GYM, beach, flexible schedule, own distance.

Challenger of Survivors: Earn Free Special Medals From us (Remote Races Series)

Nine Medals inside the box = $ 99.99 (9 medals total)

Info: race_director@runners2life.com  

       Visit us: www.runners2life.com

Facebook Group Runners2life: https://www.facebook.com/groups/1394538897435354/

Facebook Page; https://www.facebook.com/Runners2LifeOfficial/

Not t-shirts included this race in all registration categories.

Refund Policy

I agree note that Runners2life & Runinspirations reserves the right to reject any entry. We also adhere to the standard running industry policy: All entry fees are non-refundable and non-transferable also i have knwoledge this company not make returns of merchadise (t-shirts/medals/special multimedals packs) or another item inside the event. This is noted on our registration application and when you register for our events you must agree to this policy. You may not give or sell your number to another individual – doing so could result in your disqualification as well as the runner using your race number. The entry fee for this year’s event will NOT transfer to next year’s event, no exceptions. This policy stays in effect whether you are injured, have an unexpected business or family emergency, pregnancy, etc. There are NO exceptions.

Rubio Long Snapping / Chris Sailer Kicking Instructor Chris Rubio can help you to become the best snapper you can be!

In just 13 years, Chris Rubio has become the #1 snapping instructor in the country and the go-to man when a college coach needs a snapper. Colleges from across the country rely on Chris Rubio's word day in and day out on who the best snappers are in the country.

In just the last three years alone, Chris Rubio has assisted in over 350 Long Snappers earning going to college and/or the NFL. It's simple, if you want to get yourself better, noticed and into the next level: go through Rubio Long Snapping / Chris Sailer Kicking.

The point is proven time and time again as each and every year, Rubio Long Snapping puts more and more long snappers into the college football ranks.

You want the best? You have found it!

Read what a Division 1 parent has to say:

"Chris Rubio, of Rubio Long Snapping and Chris Sailer Kicking, is simply the best long snapping instructor in the world. He is a gifted instructor; an expert in the technique, art, and science of long snapping; and the number 1 resource the nation's top football programs look to when they need to find long snapping talent. His track record of developing long snappers for the collegiate level is unparalleled. The value received from attending Rubio Long Snapping Camps far exceeds anything we could have hoped for."
